Delegates
Ease
public delegate float Ease(
float current,
float initialValue,
float totalChange,
float duration
)

Represents an eased interpolation w/ respect to time.  float t, float b, float c, float d

Parameters
current
float

how long into the ease are we

initialValue
float

starting value if current were 0

totalChange
float

total change in the value (not the end value, but the end - start)

duration
float

the total amount of time (when current == duration, the returned value will == initial + totalChange)

FromAnimationCurve
public static Ease FromAnimationCurve(
AnimationCurve curve
)

Returns an Ease method that ignores start and end. Instead just returning the value in the curve for 'c', as if you called Evaluate(c).

Parameter
curve
AnimationCurve
FromVerticalScalingAnimationCurve
public static Ease FromVerticalScalingAnimationCurve(
AnimationCurve curve
)

This treats the curve as if it's a scaling factor. The vertical from 0->1 is the value s->e. And the horizontal is just 'c'. 'd' is ignored in favor of the duration of the curve.

Parameter
curve
AnimationCurve
FromScalingAnimationCurve
public static Ease FromScalingAnimationCurve(
AnimationCurve curve
)

This treats the curve as if it's a scaling factor. The vertical from 0->1 is the value s->e. And the horizontal from 0->1 is the time from c->d.
